<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-426-278  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 426 278.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  May 7 1990 n366 p3(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>286 price battle threatens; IBM expected to heat up mass-merchantmarket.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gillooly, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>IBM will adopt a mass merchandising strategy for the marketing ofits new microcomputer.andP;  The new machine, based on the Intel 80286microprocessor, will sell in the mass merchant market for ayet-to-be-determined price below the $1,000 level.andP;  Some analystspredict that this change in distribution management strategy willset off a price war within the mass marketing channel that couldaffect profit margins in the dealer channels that normally sellIBM, Packard-Bell and other blue-chip systems.andP;  Others disagreedwith this assessment, claiming that the presence of IBM in themass merchandising channel would lend it legitimacy and havelittle impact on the dealer channel.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (marketing).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     Marketing StrategyDistribution ManagementPricing PolicyMass MerchandisingMicrocomputers.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>